{"sequence":57,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:05:40.451984257Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-891dc694","body":"In `src/cli/run.rs:persist_next_step_recommendation` (line 381-383), when `std::fs::rename` fails the `.tmp` file is left behind. The counterpart in `success_reconciliation.rs:persist_next_step_hint` (line 530) cleans up with `let _ = std::fs::remove_file(&tmp_path);`. Add the same cleanup to the `run.rs` version for consistency and to avoid accumulating orphaned temp files.","dedup_key":"4f1f6e6a3ae88f918bb38442844f70fd84877a7e5fe8e4371c28bb5ed9f7c434","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":58,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:05:40.461222973Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-a55ce4c4","body":"In `success_reconciliation.rs` (lines 227-241), `select_next_milestone_bead` failures are mapped to `ReconciliationError::MilestoneUpdateFailed` which the daemon (`daemon_loop.rs:1983-2007`) treats as a task failure requiring operator intervention. But by this point the bead is already closed and synced (steps 1-2 completed). A selection failure for the *next* bead should not retroactively fail the *current* bead's reconciliation outcome. Consider wrapping the `select_next_milestone_bead` call in a best-effort handler (log + continue) similar to hint capture, or introduce a distinct error variant so the daemon can complete the current task while flagging the selection failure separately.","dedup_key":"9c09980de04ec7eb6b0f9504dd02024626d372297ca3e0f8e0ef49b6448c1e0c","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":59,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:05:40.470562308Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-c9d924f3","body":"Allow `run sync-milestone` / terminal-sync replays to re-enter selection from a blocked controller. Right now `controller_requires_terminal_task_sync` hard-returns `false` for `Blocked` in `src/cli/run.rs:690-694`, and `continue_selecting_milestone_bead_if_needed` only calls the selector when the controller is already `Selecting` in `src/cli/run.rs:731-736`. Combined with the `exact_attempt_already_terminal` gate in `src/cli/run.rs:1145-1156`, a completed bead-backed project that previously landed in `Blocked` can never be re-evaluated by rerunning `run sync-milestone`, even though the controller model explicitly supports `Blocked -> Selecting` when ready work appears in `src/contexts/milestone_record/controller.rs:965-975`. Because completed projects cannot use `run resume`, this makes blocked selection a permanent dead-end. Make terminal sync invoke the blocked-state resume path (or otherwise retry selection from `Blocked`) and add a regression test covering a completed project that becomes ready after initially blocking.","dedup_key":"b03c20be1d7dc1a6f3e49feb568cc2706c46bfb5d7b71f3e9bbcf4691a7fa263","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":60,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:05:40.479784453Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-d22f1660","body":"Stop querying `bv --robot-next` twice during daemon reconciliation. `reconcile_success` already captures and persists a `NextBeadResponse` in `src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:197-205`, but for non-final milestones it then calls `select_next_milestone_bead` in `src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:227-235`, which performs a second `bv --robot-next` call in `src/cli/run.rs:329-347` and validates/claims based on that second response in `src/cli/run.rs:538-556`. The daemon still reports the first hint in `src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1970-1974`, so the logged/persisted recommendation can differ from the bead actually claimed, and a transient failure on the second bv call can move the controller to `needs_operator` even though the first call already produced a valid recommendation. Thread the first recommendation into the selection validator (or refactor selection to accept a pre-fetched recommendation) so the recommendation that gets recorded is exactly the one that is validated and acted on.","dedup_key":"139a622f93996709adce8f2e3209406e862d24f2abd244147986505948cfbb87","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
