{"sequence":77,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:34:48.789688307Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-d830c63e","body":"`src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:229-263` swallows any error from the new next-bead selection step after a non-final reconciliation, and `src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:428-445` has already moved the controller back to `selecting` by that point. A corrupted/missing `plan.json`, controller write failure, or other `select_next_milestone_bead*()` setup error therefore leaves the milestone stuck in `selecting` with only a transient log/stdout warning. That undermines the new safe-state contract: this path should persist a `needs_operator` or `blocked` transition with the failure reason instead of leaving an apparently healthy selecting controller.","dedup_key":"acfb87b8ebaea9b1632137a63ec83ddb5a7bb0d895df3ccf91ca395ac71a6685","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
