{"sequence":94,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:53:02.104234596Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-10a320bc","body":"In `select_next_milestone_bead_from_recommendation` (src/cli/run.rs:676-679), the controller transition reason says 'requesting the next bead recommendation from bv before any claim' even though this function receives a pre-fetched recommendation and never calls bv. The `Selecting` state reason should reflect reality, e.g. 'validating a pre-fetched bv recommendation against br readiness before any claim'. This matters because operators inspect controller state reasons for debugging.","dedup_key":"972df562443f819e45d233f19a43daa381feba3ceee5a9228182d1181db44b94","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":95,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:53:02.113377630Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-cb55c3b1","body":"In `persist_next_step_recommendation` (src/cli/run.rs:354-385), all error paths use `eprintln!` for logging. In a daemon context, stderr may not be monitored. Consider using `tracing::warn!` (already used elsewhere in the codebase, e.g. success_reconciliation.rs:267) for consistency, so these failures appear in structured logs alongside the tracing infrastructure the daemon already uses.","dedup_key":"a535267831508164511b044e343f0b4f5af39e5844a591b8ed4ad3b102f3edb3","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
